Fix three nginx-layer issues: agentelo rate-limit 503s (#4, P1), missing Brotli compression (#15, P2), and missing edge cache (#17, P3).

Files to edit:
- nginx.conf (top-level repo file mounted into the nginx container — see docker-compose.yml: `./nginx.conf:/etc/nginx/nginx.conf:ro`)
- docker-compose.yml (only if you swap the nginx image to one with the Brotli module — see Brotli note below)

## Issue #4 — agentelo rate limit (P1, do this first)
Current: nginx.conf line ~17 declares `limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=global:10m rate=10r/s;` and line ~51 inside `server { ... }` applies `limit_req zone=global burst=20 nodelay;` to ALL routes. The `/agentelo/leaderboard` page renders ~99 Next.js Link rows; Next prefetches every in-viewport link concurrently and 99 simultaneous RSC requests blow past burst=20, returning 503s.

Fix: declare a second, looser zone for the agentelo subtree and apply it ONLY in the `location /agentelo/` and `location = /agentelo` blocks (currently around lines 153 and 162 of nginx.conf). Suggested: `limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=agentelo:10m rate=30r/s;` and inside the agentelo location blocks `limit_req zone=agentelo burst=200 nodelay;`. Do NOT relax the global zone for non-agentelo routes.

## Issue #15 — Brotli (P2)
`gzip on; gzip_types ...` already exists around line 12. The base `nginx:alpine` image used in docker-compose.yml does NOT ship the brotli module. Two acceptable approaches — pick the simpler one:
  (a) Swap `image: nginx:alpine` in docker-compose.yml to a brotli-enabled image such as `fholzer/nginx-brotli:latest` (Alpine-based, ships ngx_brotli built-in). Then add to nginx.conf in the http block:
      brotli on;
      brotli_comp_level 6;
      brotli_min_length 1024;
      brotli_types text/plain text/css application/javascript application/json font/woff2 image/svg+xml;
      brotli_static on;
  (b) If swapping the image is too risky for this PR, instead leave nginx.conf alone for brotli and add a single short comment block in nginx.conf documenting that brotli is desired but blocked on a custom image — and signal `flt workflow fail` describing the constraint. Prefer (a) unless something forces (b).

## Issue #17 — proxy_cache for HTML (P3)
HTML responses set `Cache-Control: s-maxage=31536000` (verify by curl) but no upstream cache exists, so it has no effect. Add an nginx `proxy_cache_path` declaration in the http block and a `proxy_cache` directive ONLY inside the `location /` block (the catch-all that proxies to Next.js, around line 174). DO NOT add proxy_cache to `/socket.io/`, `/agentelo/`, or `/admin` blocks — those must stay uncached. Suggested:
  proxy_cache_path /var/cache/nginx/html levels=1:2 keys_zone=html_cache:10m max_size=100m inactive=1h use_temp_path=off;
  # inside location / { ... }
  proxy_cache html_cache;
  proxy_cache_valid 200 1h;
  proxy_cache_use_stale error timeout updating http_500 http_502 http_503 http_504;
  proxy_cache_lock on;
  proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade $cookie_session;
  add_header X-Cache-Status $upstream_cache_status;

## Validation
- Run `nginx -t` inside the container if possible (`docker compose run --rm nginx nginx -t`) or rely on visual inspection — the config must parse.
- Read nginx.conf end-to-end after edits to confirm no duplicate directives and that the global limit_req still applies to / and other routes (only the agentelo blocks should override it).
- If you swapped the image, ensure docker-compose.yml still mounts nginx.conf at the same path (`/etc/nginx/nginx.conf:ro`).

## Commits
One commit per issue, in this order, each referencing the issue number in the subject (do NOT auto-close the issues — no `Closes #N` / `Fixes #N`; just `Refs #N`):
  - `nginx: split agentelo rate-limit zone (refs #4)`
  - `nginx: enable brotli via fholzer/nginx-brotli image (refs #15)`
  - `nginx: add proxy_cache for html catch-all route (refs #17)`

